GovMap Diff Viewer
==================

A Chrome extension that patches the govmap map website (govmap.gov.il) to render visual differences between two satellite image sources.

Features
--------

- Compare different satellite image layers
- Adjustable difference threshold
- Real-time visual diff with heatmap colors (yellow to red for changes, grayscale for unchanged areas)

Usage
-----

1. Navigate to https://www.govmap.gov.il/
2. Click the extension icon in the toolbar
3. Configure the image sources you want to compare:
   - Current: the base image layer (e.g., orto2025me)
   - Compare to: the image layer to compare against (e.g., orto2023me)
4. Adjust the threshold slider to control sensitivity
5. Click "Save" to apply changes
6. The map will reload and show differences as colored overlays

